      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/logs/agent/sessions/projects/-workspace/memory/MEMORY.md",
        "new_string": "# Django select_for_update(of) with values_list Annotation Bug - FIXED\n\n## Issue Summary\nWhen `select_for_update(of=(\"self\",))` is combined with `values_list()` containing annotation expressions (like `Concat(Value(\"Dr. \"), F(\"name\"))`), the code crashes with AttributeError on `.target.model`.\n\n## Root Cause Location\nFile: `django/db/models/sql/compiler.py`\nMethod: `get_select_for_update_of_arguments()` (lines 1405-1509)\nSpecific lines: 1424-1425 and 1440\n\n## Type Analysis\n- `Col` class (expressions.py:1287) - HAS `.target` attribute\n- `Func` class (expressions.py:1031) - NO `.target` attribute\n- Annotations use `Func` subclasses like `Concat` (functions/text.py:124)\n\n## Root Cause Explanation\n1. `get_select()` builds `self.select` as list of `(expression, alias)` tuples\n2. When `values_list()` includes annotations, expressions include `Func` objects\n3. Old code at lines 1424 & 1440 assumed ALL items have `.target` attribute\n4. Only `Col` objects (model columns) have `.target`\n5. Results in AttributeError when accessing `.target.model` on `Func` objects\n\n## Fix Applied\n\u2713 COMPLETED - Modified `/workspace/django/db/models/sql/compiler.py`\n\n### Change 1: Line 1424-1429 (_get_parent_klass_info)\nAdded: `hasattr(self.select[select_index][0], \"target\") and ...`\n\n### Change 2: Line 1444-1446 (_get_first_selected_col_from_model)\nAdded: `hasattr(self.select[select_index][0], \"target\") and ...`\n\n## Verification\nBoth hasattr() checks verified in place with grep\n\u2713 Solution document completed at /logs/agent/solution.md\n\u2713 Fixed file at /workspace/django/db/models/sql/compiler.py\n",
